text: Siazan () is a raion in Azerbaijan. The capital is Siyəzən. The region has many Tats who speak the Tat language. The word Siyazan means "black female" in Tat. In 2010 there were 37,900 people. ==References== Category:Districts of Azerbaijan Category:Guba-Khachmaz Economic Region
title: Siyazan District
